Before I go into this review... please remember, this review is based on my experience and the food that was served on the day of delivery. Taking that into consideration...  I do not like writing a hurtful review but this was simply not a good food experience.  We ordered here through "prime" and had it delivered.  So sorry to say this meal was not worth the cost of the food and delivery. Neither of the meals actually tasted like anything.  The medium hot was not spicy at all in either meals as well.  A very bland taste experience which left nothing to.... well... nothing is all I can say.  The only vegetable you could actually "taste" was the mushroom. We expected some type of sauce or a thickened liquid to go with the meal.  When we transferred the food from the to-go containers to the bowls, it seemed as if it was merely water or the remnants of the noddle broth.  Even if it was the broth, this had no taste either.  Again, a review can be hit and miss as you can see from the other reviews in and around this one.  All I can say is "I" will not be ordering from here again.  But, I see others who have given this establishment glowing reviews so all I can say is, try for yourself and I hope you have a 5 star visit!

I've been Yummy Thai for many years. They're food is great, particularly their curries and Pad Thai. I have noticed the last couple of years the customer service when it comes to take out has failed numerous times. It's difficult to call in order due to them not answering the phone. So, I tried ordering online, turns out that failed as well. I placed a order around 11:30 a.m online. When I went to pick it up, they informed me my order was cancelled. What they lacked on telling me was why my order was cancelled, and I wish I would've known before I placed my order on person and waited an additional 20 minutes. My order was cancelled due to them not answering the phone after the several phone calls, the 3rd party they use for online orders, to confirm my order. When I read my email and showed them my order was cancelled due to them not answering, I pretty much received and oh well response. Not only does 3rd party call to confirm, but also send an alert online on a tablet they have placed next to their phone. I wish I could say this was the first time this occurred, but it's not.

Very nice place. Almost all meals can be made with your favorite meat/veggies/tofu, very friendly waiters/waitresses, and not too long of a waiting time. I'm vegetarian, and this place has tons of choices.  Also good for vegans because they use coconut milk in their curries and I've asked before, they don't use oyster/fish sauce (probably still best to ask).  This is my go to place now, as they do carry out if I want to eat at home.
